A manga magazine launched by the trio of Nobuhiko Horie, Tetsuo Hara and Tsukasa Hojo (all best-known for their time working for Weekly Shonen Jump where Horie was editor-in-chief and Hara and Hojo had both published some of the most popular titles of the 80's and 90's).

It lasted from 2001 to 2010 and featured a variety of titles with Hara and Hojo each contributing a series for the magazine's full run (Sōten no Ken and Angel Heart, respectively).
